    "faq_section_pea": {
      "type": "collapsible-content",
      "blocks": {
        "faq_q1": {
          "type": "collapsible_row",
          "settings": {
            "heading": "How long until I see results?",
            "icon": "none",
            "row_content": "<p>PEA works cumulatively. Most users notice improvements in comfort and nerve sensitivity between weeks 2 and 4 — but the biggest gains happen between day 30 and day 60. A 2024 meta-analysis confirmed that results continue building through the second month. Give it the full 60 days.<\/p>",
            "page": ""
          }
        },
        "faq_q2": {
          "type": "collapsible_row",
          "settings": {
            "heading": "What is the correct dosage?",
            "icon": "none",
            "row_content": "<p>Take 2 veggie capsules daily, preferably with a meal. PEA is fat-soluble, so taking it with food that contains some healthy fat improves absorption. Consistent daily use is essential — do not skip days.<\/p>",
            "page": ""
          }
        },
        "faq_q3": {
          "type": "collapsible_row",
          "settings": {
            "heading": "What exactly is PEA?",
            "icon": "none",
            "row_content": "<p>Palmitoylethanolamide is a fatty acid amide your body already produces naturally when tissues are under stress or irritation. Supplementing with micronized PEA supports the same pathway — helping calm nerve sensitivity and support healthy inflammatory balance. It is body-own, not exotic.<\/p>",
            "page": ""
          }
        },
        "faq_q4": {
          "type": "collapsible_row",
          "settings": {
            "heading": "How is this different from CBD?",
            "icon": "none",
            "row_content": "<p>PEA and CBD are often compared because they interact with overlapping pathways. But PEA is body-own — your system already makes it — and it is non-psychoactive, non-THC, and free from the regulatory and quality-control concerns that come with CBD products. PEA also has a significantly larger randomized controlled trial evidence base.<\/p>",
            "page": ""
          }
        },
        "faq_q5": {
          "type": "collapsible_row",
          "settings": {
            "heading": "Are there any side effects?",
            "icon": "none",
            "row_content": "<p>PEA is generally well tolerated. A small number of users report mild nausea, which can usually be avoided by taking capsules with food. If you experience any discomfort, start with 1 capsule daily and gradually increase. If you have any underlying health conditions, consult your healthcare provider before use.<\/p>",
            "page": ""
          }
        },
        "faq_q6": {
          "type": "collapsible_row",
          "settings": {
            "heading": "Can I take it with other supplements or medications?",
            "icon": "none",
            "row_content": "<p>PEA is generally considered safe alongside most supplements. If you are taking prescription medication — particularly for pain, inflammation, or neurological conditions — consult your healthcare provider before use.<\/p>",
            "page": ""
          }
        },
        "faq_q7": {
          "type": "collapsible_row",
          "settings": {
            "heading": "Why does it need to be micronized?",
            "icon": "none",
            "row_content": "<p>PEA is naturally poorly soluble. Micronization reduces the particle size, which dramatically improves surface area and bioavailability. This is why virtually all the clinical research uses micronized or ultramicronized formats — and why cheaper, non-micronized PEA products may underperform.<\/p>",
            "page": ""
          }
        },
        "faq_q8": {
          "type": "collapsible_row",
          "settings": {
            "heading": "Why 60 days and not 30?",
            "icon": "none",
            "row_content": "<p>Because the evidence shows the biggest gains happen in month two. A 2024 meta-analysis found a 35.1% reduction in the first month — then a further 35.4% reduction from day 30 to day 60. Stopping at 30 days means leaving the best results on the table. Our 60-day guarantee is built around this exact window.<\/p>",
            "page": ""
          }
        }
      },
